nal loss, this book maintains that, for Derrida, salutation, greeting, and welcoming is resistant to the economy of salvation. This resistance calls for what Derrida refers to as a "spectro-poetics" devoted to and assigned to the other's singularity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDeath. 0aLoss (Psychology). 0aOther (Philosophy). 0aSalvation. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847822740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438478227423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438478227/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles